<h3>A Simple RESTful example</h3>
<p>
	This webapp is a simple RESTful application example for students in computing science.<br/>
	It was designed with Java EE Technologies (Servlet, JAX-RS, JPA) and hosted by Google&nbsp;App&nbsp;Engine.
</p>
<p>
	The documentation of the REST API is available in the side bar to the right.
</p>
<p>
	To consume web services, you can use <a href="http://curl.haxx.se/">cURL</a>, develop your own REST client, 
	or use one available as plugin for your browser.
	The best known are:
	<ul>
		<li><a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/fhjcajmcbmldlhcimfajhfbgofnpcjmb">Simple REST Client</a> for Google Chrome</li>
		<li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/restclient/">RESTClient</a> for Mozilla Firefox</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<p>
	Source codes are available on GitHub. Click into the logo inside the side bar to get there.
</p>
